	(99,'Beer','Upholstery','<li>White vinegar</li>\n  <li>Rubbing alcohol </li>','<li>Mix one tablespoon of white vinegar with 2/3 cup       of rubbing alcohol.</li>\n  <li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with       the vinegar/alcohol solution.</li>\n  <li>Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n  <li>Repeat Steps 2 and 3 until the stain disappears. </li>','<h3>What you will need</h3>\n				<ul>\n  <li>White vinegar</li>\n  <li>Rubbing alcohol </li>\n</ul>\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				<ol>\n  <li>Mix one tablespoon of white vinegar with 2/3 cup       of rubbing alcohol.</li>\n  <li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with       the vinegar/alcohol solution.</li>\n  <li>Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n  <li>Repeat Steps 2 and 3 until the stain disappears. </li>\n</ol>\n				\n					<h4>Or</h4>\n				\n				\n			\n				<h3>What you will need</h3>\n				<ul>\n    <li>Detergent</li>\n  </ul>\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				  <ol>\n    <li>Mix one (1) tablespoon of liquid dishwashing       detergent with two (2) cups of cool water.</li>\n    <li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with       the detergent solution.</li>\n    <li>Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n    <li>Repeat Steps 2 and 3 until the stain disappears. </li>\n    <li>Sponge with cold water and blot dry to remove the       detergent solution.</li>\n  </ol>','35.jpg');
