	(110,'Tar','Carpet','<li>Clean absorbent towels</li><li>Carpet shampoo</li><li>Dull knife</li><li>Vacuum</li>','<li>Remove excess material by blotting up liquids       with a clean absorbent towel and scraping up solids with a dull edge of a       knife.  </li>\n  <li>Sponge lightly with cool water and blot several       times.  Apply diluted carpet shampoo       (1 part liquid carpet shampoo to 4 parts water) with a brush or       towel.  </li>\n  <li>Let the area dry thoroughly; then vacuum.  Repeat if necessary. </li>','<div class=\"boxChem\"><h3>Chemical solvents and supplies</h3><ul><li>Clean absorbent towels</li><li>Carpet shampoo</li><li>Dull knife</li><li>Vacuum</li></ul></div> <ol>\n  <li>Remove excess material by blotting up liquids       with a clean absorbent towel and scraping up solids with a dull edge of a       knife.  </li>\n  <li>Sponge lightly with cool water and blot several       times.  Apply diluted carpet shampoo       (1 part liquid carpet shampoo to 4 parts water) with a brush or       towel.  </li>\n  <li>Let the area dry thoroughly; then vacuum.  Repeat if necessary. </li>\n</ol>\n				\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				<ol>\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n				</ol>','142.jpg');
