	(283,'Mud','Upholstery','<li>Detergent</li>','<li>Mix one (1) tablespoon of liquid dishwashing       detergent with two (2) cups of cool water.</li>\n    <li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with       the detergent solution.</li>\n    <li>Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n    <li>Repeat Steps 2 and 3 until the stain disappears. </li>\n    <li>Sponge with cold water and blot dry to remove the       detergent solution.</li>','<h3>What you will need</h3>\n				<ul>\n    <li>Detergent</li>\n  </ul>\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				  <ol>\n    <li>Mix one (1) tablespoon of liquid dishwashing       detergent with two (2) cups of cool water.</li>\n    <li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with       the detergent solution.</li>\n    <li>Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n    <li>Repeat Steps 2 and 3 until the stain disappears. </li>\n    <li>Sponge with cold water and blot dry to remove the       detergent solution.</li>\n  </ol>','19.jpg');
