	(314,'Tomato-based products','Upholstery','<li>White vinegar</li>\n	<li>Prewash stain remover</li>\n    <li>detergent</li>','<li>Sponge the area with cool water, then sponge area  using a solution of equal parts of white vinegar and cool water.  </li>\n  <li>Rinse with cool water.  </li>\n  <li>Cover stained area with a pad of absorbent material  dampened with a prewash stain remover, liquid laundry detergent or a paste made  of granular detergent and water. </li>\n  <li>Change absorbent pad of material as it picks up the  stain.  </li>\n  <li>Keep stain moist for up to 30 minutes. </li>\n  <li>Rinse with water.   Products with enzymes should not be used on wool or silk fabrics. </li>','<h3>What you will need</h3>\n				<ul>\n	<li>White vinegar</li>\n	<li>Prewash stain remover</li>\n    <li>detergent</li>\n</ul>\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				<ol>\n  <li>Sponge the area with cool water, then sponge area  using a solution of equal parts of white vinegar and cool water.  </li>\n  <li>Rinse with cool water.  </li>\n  <li>Cover stained area with a pad of absorbent material  dampened with a prewash stain remover, liquid laundry detergent or a paste made  of granular detergent and water. </li>\n  <li>Change absorbent pad of material as it picks up the  stain.  </li>\n  <li>Keep stain moist for up to 30 minutes. </li>\n  <li>Rinse with water.   Products with enzymes should not be used on wool or silk fabrics. </li>\n</ol>','96.jpg');
