	(332,'Hair gel','Carpet','<li>Dry Cleaning solvent</li>    \n    <li>Detergent</li>\n    <li>White vinegar</li>','<li>Scrape off excess foreign material.</li>\n					\n					\n						<li>Sprinkle baking soda, cornstarch or other absorbent in the stain. Let stand for 10 or 15 minutes, and then vacuum.</li>\n					\n					\n						<li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with the dry cleaning solvent.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>Blot until the solvent is absorbed.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>If the stain remains, mix one tablespoon of liquid dishwashing detergent and one tablespoon of white vinegar with two cups of warm water. Sponge the stain with this solution. Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>Sponge with cold water and blot dry to remove the detergent/vinegar solution. </li>','<h3>What you will need</h3>\n					<ul>\n    <li>Dry Cleaning solvent</li>    \n    <li>Detergent</li>\n    <li>White vinegar</li>\n</ul>\n				\n				\n				<h3>Steps to Clean</h3>\n				<ol>\n					\n					\n						<li>Scrape off excess foreign material.</li>\n					\n					\n						<li>Sprinkle baking soda, cornstarch or other absorbent in the stain. Let stand for 10 or 15 minutes, and then vacuum.</li>\n					\n					\n						<li>Using a clean white cloth, sponge the stain with the dry cleaning solvent.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>Blot until the solvent is absorbed.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>If the stain remains, mix one tablespoon of liquid dishwashing detergent and one tablespoon of white vinegar with two cups of warm water. Sponge the stain with this solution. Blot until the liquid is absorbed.</li>\n					\n					\n					\n						<li>Sponge with cold water and blot dry to remove the detergent/vinegar solution. </li>\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n				</ol>','169.jpg');
